(2631, 1143, 'Kevin Alameda', 'Vice President', 'kevin@clipperoil.com', '+1 858 229 9755', 'kevin.alameda', 'Kevin Alameda is in charge of the day-to-day operations at Clipper Oil. He is responsible for ensuring adequate inventory levels, growing the customer base and expanding Clipper Oil into new markets.\r\n\r\nKevin has been with Clipper Oil since 2006 and has been actively involved in expanding Clipper’s operations throughout the globe. Prior to his role at Clipper Oil, Kevin was the Manager of Procurement for Bumble Bee Seafoods.\r\n\r\nKevin received a B.A. in Economics & Political Science from the University of Michigan.', ''),
(2632, 1143, 'Eric Shahtaji', 'Director of Sales', 'eric@clipperoil.com', '+1 708 305 4044', 'eric.clipperoil', 'Eric Shahtaji is responsible for business development out of Clipper Oil’s headquarters in San Diego, as well as quoting competitive bunker and lubricant prices to Clipper Oil’s worldwide clientele.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Clipper Oil, Eric worked as a logistics consultant for a shipping and freight management firm.\r\n\r\nEric received a B.A. in International Studies & International Business from the University of Iowa and is fluent in English and Spanish.', NULL),
(2633, 1143, 'Kyle Olson', 'International Fuel Trader', 'kyle@clipperoil.com', '+1 218 348 9667', '', 'Kyle Olson delivers competitive bunker and lubricant pricing to Clipper Oil\'s existing customer base and prospective clients.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining the Clipper Oil team in 2017, Kyle lived in Minnesota and worked as a Commodity Trader dealing with bulk physical commodities for renewable fuels and feed industries.\r\n\r\nKyle received a B.S. in Applied Economics with an emphasis in Finance from the University of Minnesota.', NULL),
(2634, 1143, 'Chad Indihar ', 'Business Operations Manager', 'chad@clipperoil.com', '+1 858 733 1226', 'chad.indihar', 'Chad Indihar is responsible for Clipper Oil\'s physical markets including American Samoa, Marshall Islands and the Federated States of Micronesia. Chad is also responsible for managing Clipper Oil\'s Operations Department.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Clipper Oil, Chad worked in financial services and business operations management.\r\n\r\nChad received a B.S. in Finance from California State University, Long Beach.', NULL),
(2635, 1143, 'Emily Wilson', 'International Fuel Trader', 'emily@clipperoil.com', '+1 617 401 6881', '', 'Emily Wilson serves Clipper Oil’s clients worldwide, with an unconditional determination to deliver competitively priced fuel and lubricant oil that’s both on-time and under-budget.\r\nShe began her career at Clipper Oil in 2018 as an Operations Coordinator. In this position, she was the primary point of contact Clipper Oil’s clientele and ensured timely delivery of Clipper’s products worldwide.\r\n\r\nEmily received a B.A. in Economics and a Master\'s Degree in Public Administration from the University of Connecticut.', NULL),
(2636, 1143, 'Austin Nicholson', 'Sales & Marketing Representative', 'austin@clipperoil.com', '+1 858 761 4091', '', 'Austin Nicholson is responsible for marketing and project management at Clipper Oil. Austin is also in charge of many of Clipper Oil’s inland fuel requirements and keeping Clipper Oil’s database up-to-date.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Clipper Oil, Austin worked for an international accounting firm.\r\n\r\nAustin received a B.A. in International Business with an emphasis in Latin American studies from San Diego State University and is fluent in English and Spanish.', NULL),
(2637, 1143, 'Lori Green', 'Office Manager/Accountant', 'lori@clipperoil.com', '', '', 'Lori Green serves as the Office Manager/Accountant at Clipper Oil where she ensures that the daily administrative operations run smoothly. Lori joined Clipper Oil in 2018 and is actively involved with the company’s credit management procedure.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Clipper Oil, Lori spent several years serving as an Office Manager, Executive Assistant and Bookkeeper in the Information Technology industry in San Diego.\r\n\r\nLori received a B.S. from Colorado State University and has a Professional Certificate in Accounting Management from San Diego State University.', NULL),
(2638, 1143, 'Natasha Susanto', 'Staff Accountant', 'natasha@clipperoil.com', '+1 619 997 2919', '', 'Natasha Susanto is responsible for performing professional accounting duties in the analysis, preparation and maintenance of Clipper Oil’s financial records. This includes processing day-to-day transactions and reconciliations for the American Samoa, San Diego and Singapore offices.\r\n\r\nPrior to her role at Clipper Oil, Natasha worked as a business transition specialist for a financial services company.\r\n\r\nNatasha received a B.A. in Economics with a Business Minor from the University of California, San Diego and is fluent in English and Indonesian.', NULL),
